What is assembly?
Assembly is a low level language that gives you exactly what code you need, and complete control.
What is it good for?
Writing device driver, updating OS design, aviation industry, medicine.
How is assembly different than Java?
It is not portable, it is more difficult to learn, but gives complete control, and only the info you need. 
What are differences between high level and low level languages?
High level is easier to learn and read, but low level are faster.
Which type is Java? How do you know, i.e., what characteristics does it have of that language type?
High level. It is portable, uses alot of english, and is easy to modify.
Which type is Assembly? How do you know, i.e., what characteristics does it have of that language type?
low level, difficult to under stand,
